  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati</strong>&nbsp;<strong>rice</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> water to a pot with a lid&nbsp;and bring to the boil over a high heat, once&nbsp;boiling, add the <strong>kaffir</strong>&nbsp;<strong>lime leaves</strong>, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7 and boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown&nbsp;</strong><strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with 2-3 tbsp <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>curry powder</strong> and stir for 30 sec, until the oil and spice form a wet, paste-like consistency</p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium-low, add the <strong>onion</strong> and cook for 5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the&nbsp;<strong>green beans</strong>&nbsp;in half</p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>onion</strong> has softened, add the<strong>&nbsp;chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> then cook for a further 4 min</p>\r\n<p>Tip: watch the garlic closely to prevent burning!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong>, the&nbsp;<strong>green beans</strong>, <strong>fish sauce</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>sugar</strong> to the pan</p>\r\n<p>Increase the heat to medium, cover and cook for 7-10 min or until the green beans are tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>fish</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p>\r\n<p>Drizzle with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 10 min or until the fish is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Tip:&nbsp;your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/379.-379__-step-6-x400.jpg",
